A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Criminal Law – Concealment of Death and Disturbing and Dismembering
3 Human Remains
4 FOR the purpose of prohibiting a person, with the intent to conceal the death of another,
5 from failing to notify emergency medical services or law enforcement regarding the
6 death, committing certain destructive acts to any part of human remains, or burying
7 or otherwise disposing of a dead body; prohibiting a person from aiding or abetting
8 another in committing a violation of this Act; and generally relating to the
9 prohibition against the intentional concealment of a death.
10 BY adding to
11 Article – Criminal Law
12 Section 10–405
13 Annotated Code of Maryland
14 (2021 Replacement Volume and 2024 Supplement)
15 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
16 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
17 Article – Criminal Law
18 10–405.
19 (A) A PERSON MAY NOT, WITH THE INTENT TO CONCEAL THE DEATH OF
20 ANOTHER:
21 (1) FAIL TO CONTACT EMERGENCY MEDICAL SERVICES OR LAW
22 ENFORCEMENT REGARDING THE DEATH OF THE PERSON;
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
