2 SENATE BILL 394
1 (2) KNOWINGLY AND WILLFULLY DISMEMBER, DESTROY, REMOVE, OR
2 OTHERWISE OBLITERATE BY ANY MEANS ANY PORTION OF HUMAN REMAINS; OR
3 (3) BURY OR OTHERWISE DISPOSE OF A DEAD BODY.
4 (B) A PERSON MAY NOT AID OR ABET ANOTHER IN COMMITTING A
5 VIOLATION OF THIS SECTION.
6 (C) A PERSON WHO VIOLATES THIS SECTION IS GUILTY OF A FELONY AND
7 ON CONVICTION IS SUBJECT TO IMPRISONMENT NOT EXCEEDING 10 YEARS.
8 (D) A SENTENCE IMPOSED UNDER THIS SECTION SHALL BE CONSECUTIVE
9 TO AND NOT CONCURRENT WITH ANY OTHER SENTENCE IMPOSED FOR ANY OTHER
10 CRIME BASED ON THE ACT ESTABLISHING THE VIOLATION OF THIS SECTION.
11 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
12 October 1, 2025.

